I"	<p>Risk has hit the media in connection with the side effects of the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/regulatory-approval-of-covid-19-vaccine-astrazeneca">Oxford-AstraZenica vaccine</a>. But in the discussion about the risk of <a href="https://www.bmj.com/content/372/bmj.n774">blood clots</a> the benefits of the vaccine have been drowned out.  The media always concentrates on risk, after all it makes good headlines, but what are we missing when the benefits are not included in the discussion?</p>
